HEADWORD: Cicatricle
<hw>Cic"a*tri`cle</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>cicatricule</ets>, fr. L. <ets>cicatricula</ets> a small scar, fr.
<ets>cicatrix</ets> a scar.]</ety> <fld>(Biol.)</fld> <def>The
germinating point in the embryo of a seed; the point in the yolk of an
egg at which development begins.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cicatrisive</ent>⟦br⟧
